# {{ s.global.inner.application_name }}

## Overview

{{ s.global.inner.application_name }} is a Rust desktop application.
Organization: {{ s.global.inner.organisation_name }} ({{ s.global.inner.organisation_domain }}).
Generated by Qleany v{{ s.system.inner.version }}.

## Architecture

This project follows **Clean Architecture** with **Package by Feature** (Vertical Slice) organization.
Each feature is a separate crate containing all its related code. Entities and shared infrastructure live in the `common` crate.

Dependency direction: **UI -> Controllers -> Use Cases -> Repositories -> Database**

- **Entities** -- Domain objects with identity (structs with `#[derive(Serialize, Deserialize)]` in `common/src/entities.rs`)
- **Use Cases** -- Single-purpose operations encapsulating business logic
- **DTOs** -- Data transfer structs at boundaries
- **Repositories** -- Data access abstraction (one per entity)
- **Controllers** -- Expose use cases to the UI layer
- **Unit of Work** -- Transaction boundary wrapping repository access

## Tech Stack

- **Language**: Rust 2024 edition
- **Database**: redb (embedded key-value store, WAL mode)
{%- if s.ui.inner.rust_slint %}
- **UI**: Slint
{%- endif %}
{%- if s.ui.inner.rust_cli %}
- **CLI**: Clap
{%- endif %}
{%- if s.ui.inner.rust_ios or s.ui.inner.rust_android %}
- **Mobile bridge**: UniFFI (FFI bindings for {% if s.ui.inner.rust_ios %}iOS/Swift{% endif %}{% if s.ui.inner.rust_ios and s.ui.inner.rust_android %} and {% endif %}{% if s.ui.inner.rust_android %}Android/Kotlin{% endif %})
{%- endif %}
- **Async**: std threads + flume channels for events
- **Error handling**: `anyhow::Result` (use cases throw `anyhow!` errors; UoW handles rollback)
- **Build**: Cargo workspace
- **Proc macros**: `#[macros::uow_action]` for UoW trait method generation

