## Key Patterns

### Unit of Work (UoW)

Each use case receives a UoW that wraps a database transaction. The UoW provides typed access to entity repositories via Rust proc macros (`#[macros::uow_action]`).

**Trait macros** (in `use_cases/{use_case}_uc.rs`, generates trait methods). **Implementation macros** (in `units_of_work/{use_case}_uow.rs`) use the same macros. Both files must declare the same set of entity operations.

#### Read-only actions (use with `QueryUnitOfWork`)

| Macro | Generated method |
|-------|------------------|
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetRO")]` | `get_{snake}(id) -> Result<Option<Name>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetMultiRO")]` | `get_{snake}_multi(ids) -> Result<Vec<Option<Name>>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetAllRO")]` | `get_all_{snake}() -> Result<Vec<Name>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetRelationshipRO")]` | `get_{snake}_relationship(id, field) -> Result<Vec<EntityId>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetRelationshipManyRO")]` | `get_{snake}_relationship_many(ids, field) -> Result<HashMap<EntityId, Vec<EntityId>>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetRelationshipCountRO")]` | `get_{snake}_relationship_count(id, field) -> Result<usize>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetRelationshipInRangeRO")]` | `get_{snake}_relationship_in_range(id, field, offset, limit) -> Result<Vec<EntityId>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetRelationshipsFromRightIdsRO")]` | `get_{snake}_relationships_from_right_ids(field, right_ids) -> Result<Vec<(EntityId, Vec<EntityId>)>>` |

#### Read-write actions (use with `CommandUnitOfWork`)

| Macro | Generated method |
|-------|------------------|
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "Get")]` | `get_{snake}(id) -> Result<Option<Name>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetMulti")]` | `get_{snake}_multi(ids) -> Result<Vec<Option<Name>>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetAll")]` | `get_all_{snake}() -> Result<Vec<Name>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "Create")]` | `create_{snake}(entity, owner_id, index) -> Result<Name>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "CreateMulti")]` | `create_{snake}_multi(entities, owner_id, index) -> Result<Vec<Name>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "CreateOrphan")]` | `create_orphan_{snake}(entity) -> Result<Name>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "CreateOrphanMulti")]` | `create_orphan_{snake}_multi(entities) -> Result<Vec<Name>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "Update")]` | `update_{snake}(entity) -> Result<Name>` (scalar fields only) |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "UpdateMulti")]` | `update_{snake}_multi(entities) -> Result<Vec<Name>>` (scalar fields only) |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "UpdateWithRelationships")]` | `update_with_relationships_{snake}(entity) -> Result<Name>` (scalars + relationships) |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "UpdateWithRelationshipsMulti")]` | `update_with_relationships_{snake}_multi(entities) -> Result<Vec<Name>>` (scalars + relationships) |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "Remove")]` | `remove_{snake}(id) -> Result<()>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "RemoveMulti")]` | `remove_{snake}_multi(ids) -> Result<()>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetRelationship")]` | `get_{snake}_relationship(id, field) -> Result<Vec<EntityId>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetRelationshipMany")]` | `get_{snake}_relationship_many(ids, field) -> Result<HashMap<EntityId, Vec<EntityId>>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetRelationshipCount")]` | `get_{snake}_relationship_count(id, field) -> Result<usize>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetRelationshipInRange")]` | `get_{snake}_relationship_in_range(id, field, offset, limit) -> Result<Vec<EntityId>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetRelationshipsFromRightIds")]` | `get_{snake}_relationships_from_right_ids(field, right_ids) -> Result<Vec<(EntityId, Vec<EntityId>)>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "SetRelationship")]` | `set_{snake}_relationship(id, field, ids) -> Result<()>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "SetRelationshipMulti")]` | `set_{snake}_relationship_multi(field, relationships) -> Result<()>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "MoveRelationship")]` | `move_{snake}_relationship(id, field, ids_to_move, new_index) -> Result<Vec<EntityId>>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "Snapshot")]` | `snapshot_{snake}(ids) -> Result<EntityTreeSnapshot>` |
| `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "Restore")]` | `restore_{snake}(snap) -> Result<()>` |

#### Thread-safe (for long operations)

Add `thread_safe = true` to any macro: `#[macros::uow_action(entity = "Name", action = "GetRO", thread_safe = true)]`

### Relationship Fields

Each entity with forward relationships generates a typed enum `{Entity}RelationshipField` (e.g., `WorkspaceRelationshipField::Entities`). UoW relationship methods take this enum as the `field` parameter:

```rust
let child_ids = uow.get_workspace_relationship(ws_id, WorkspaceRelationshipField::Entities)?;
uow.set_workspace_relationship(ws_id, WorkspaceRelationshipField::Entities, &new_ids)?;
```

Entities with an owner also have `get_relationships_from_owner(owner_id)` and `set_relationships_in_owner(owner_id, ids)` helpers on the repository.

### Controllers

Entity controllers are auto-generated with full CRUD operations. Feature controllers are generated with stubs for custom use cases.

### Events

Entity changes emit events through `EventHub`. `EventBuffer` defers event emission until after transaction commit.

Feature use cases emit events via `uow.publish_{use_case_snake}_event(ids, data)` after commit. This method is declared on the UoW trait and implemented in the UoW to send directly through the `EventHub`. The `ids` and `data` parameters let you attach context to the event.

### Undo/Redo

The `UndoRedoManager` manages command stacks of `UndoRedoCommand` objects. Controllers wrap undoable use cases into commands.

For **auto-generated entity CRUD** use cases, `undo()` and `redo()` are pre-built using `EntityTreeSnapshot`.

For **custom feature use cases**, the developer must implement the `UndoRedoCommand` trait (`undo()`, `redo()`, `as_any()`) on the use case struct.

### Long Operations

Long-running use cases implement the `LongOperation` trait. They run on a background thread managed by `LongOperationManager`, with progress reporting and cancellation support via `Arc<AtomicBool>`.

## Conventions

- **Entity names**: PascalCase in code, snake_case in file paths
- **File naming**: `{snake_name}_uc.rs`, `{snake_name}_uow.rs`, `dtos.rs`
- **One use case per file**: each operation gets its own `.rs` file
- **Strong relationships**: cascade remove (owner removes children)
- **Weak relationships**: reference only (no cascade)
- **Error handling**: return `anyhow::Result`, use `anyhow!("message")` for business errors
- **Prefix path**: `{{ s.global.prefix }}`
